  <title xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Association for the Prevention of Torture: core contributions, engagement</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2" xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">APT is an independent international NGO aiming at preventing the use of torture globally and a long-term cooperation partner of the Government of Denmark. The organization focuses on torture prevention rather than on individual cases and public condemnation of particular states. This enables the organisation to collaborate with a wide range of relevant actors, inter alia state authorities, police services, the judiciary, national institutions and academics. The project focuses mainly on human rights and torture prevention. The key strategic objectives are (1) strengthened legal and policy frameworks, (2) improved detention practices, and (3) strengthened public oversight.</narrative>
  </description>
